text: Latta is an unincorporated community and census-designated place in Pontotoc County, Oklahoma, United States. Its population was 1,172 as of 2016. Oklahoma State Highway 1 passes through the community. ==Geography== According to the U.S. Census Bureau, the community has an area of , all of it land. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Pontotoc County, Oklahoma Category:Unincorporated communities in Oklahoma Category:Census- designated places in Pontotoc County, Oklahoma Category:Census-designated places in Oklahoma
